Chop the @cherry tomatoes{1} into quarters. Slice the @courgette{1} in half lengthways, then slice each half lengthways into 3 slices. Now cube the courgette and grate the @parmesan cheese{2}.

Chop up ⅔ of the @basil{½} and all the @pine nuts{2} as finely as possible.

> Everything should be smaller than a grain of rice.

Mix the basil and pine nuts with @crème fraîche{3%tbsp}. Mix in the parmesan and @salt{¼%tsp}.

Heat @oil{½%tbsp} in a #non-stick pan{} on high heat. When hot, cook off your courgette for ~{4-5%minutes} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Once browned, keep to the side for later.

Cook your @British smoked bacon lardons{¼} for ~{2%minutes} with @olive oil{2%tsp} until crispy, then add the cherry tomatoes for another ~{4%minutes}.

Remove everything from the pan and add @olive oil{2%tsp} on medium-high heat. Fry the @gnocchi{3} for ~{8%minutes} until it's crispy around the edges.

Add two handfuls of @baby spinach{½} to the gnocchi. Stir together until the spinach wilts.